              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Scalability"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Exponential state space"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Scales with context length"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Adaptability"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Requires re-planning when model changes"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Flexible \u2014 handles novel goals"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Best for"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Well-defined domains, safety-critical tasks"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Open-ended, natural-language goals"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When Classical Planning Concepts Help LLM Agents"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Precondition checking:"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " before executing a step, verify its preconditions are met. Implement as a guard function that checks the current world state against the step's expected inputs."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Effect tracking:"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " after each step, update a state dictionary with the step's effects. This gives the executor a consistent view of what is known to be true."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Goal regression:"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " work backward from the goal to identify which steps are actually necessary. Equivalent to backward chaining and removes unnecessary steps from an over-specified plan."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Cycle detection:"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " if the state after a step matches an earlier state, the plan is in a loop. Track visited states (as frozensets) and fail fast."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "STRIPS"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " represents planning as: initial state, goal, and operators with preconditions, add effects, and delete effects. States are sets of ground atoms."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Forward BFS"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " is complete and optimal but exponential in state space size. Practical only for small domains."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "A* with h-add"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " uses a relaxed planning graph to guide search efficiently, scaling to larger domains."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "LLMs can formulate STRIPS problems"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " from natural language; the symbolic planner then finds the plan rigorously."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Classical planning concepts"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " (precondition checking, effect tracking, goal regression) improve LLM agent robustness even when full formal planning is not used."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}